A 24-hour strike by Belgian publicemployees protesting against a government pay offer disruptedtransport and hit ferry services and shipping, port and unionofficials said.    Some cross-Channel ferry services from Ostend werecancelled, the local news agency Belga said.    An Antwerp port authority spokesman said electricians cameout in support, reducing ship movements to a trickle. Unionssaid Ghent and other major Belgian ports were also hit.    Few trains were running and some early morning flights bySabena, Belgian's national airline, were cancelled. Reuter&#3;